==English==

===Etymology===
Feld, field (from Middle High German veld, from Old High German feld) + Spath, spar + Oid, like or resembling.

===Noun===
'''feldspathoid'''
# {{mineralogy}} A small group of [[igneous]], [[plutonic]], and [[volcanic]] [[mineral]]s formed in [[magma]] that did not contain enough [[silica]] to satisfy all the chemical bonds.  Feldspathoids are silica-poor variants of the [[feldspar]] group.

*Varieties:
# [[leucite]]
# [[nepheline]]

====Related terms====
:''See'' [[rock]], [[mineral]]

===Adjective===
'''felthspathoid'''
# {{mineralogy}} Resembling a [[feldspar]].

